About YRF Spy Universe:
YRF Spy Universe is a first of its kind cinematic universe of spy thriller films in India. The first film in the universe, "Ek Tha Tiger", starring Salman Khan and Katrina Kaif was released in 2012, followed by its sequel "Tiger Zinda Hai" in 2017. The third film in the universe, "War" was released in 2019 and starred Hrithik Roshan and Tiger Shroff in pivotal roles. "Pathaan" was the fourth instalment in the Spy Universe franchise which was released in 2023 starring Shah Rukh Khan, Deepika Padukone and John Abraham. "Tiger 3", the fifth instalment in the YRF Spy Universe and the third film in the Tiger series, starring Salman Khan, Katrina Kaif and Emraan Hashmi, released in 2023. "War 2" is the sixth film of the YRF Spy Universe franchise and will release on 14 August 2025. The film stars two of the greatest cinematic icons Hrithik Roshan and NTR, with Kiara Advani in the lead and is directed by Ayan Mukerji. “Alpha”, the seventh instalment in the franchise and Hindi cinema's first female-led YRF Spy Universe film, starring Alia Bhatt and Sharvari, is set to release on 25 December 2025.

#cricketlive #cricketmatch #indvsseng 

IND vs ENG, 5th Test Day 3 Live Commentary | INDIA vs ENGLAND Live | Live Match Today | IND Batting

INDIA VS ENGALND Test 5 Day 2 Preview :


India could only add 20 runs to their overnight first-innings score, losing the remaining four wickets in the first half of the morning session. Karun Nair top-scored for the visitors with 57 runs to his name. Gus Atkinson picked up three of those four wickets to complete a five-wicket haul on his return in whites.

England openers Zak Crawley and Ben Duckett came out all guns blazing, unleashing the BazBall approach right from the outset as they took on the Indian pacers with authority. The duo raced to 92 runs in just 12.5 overs before Akash Deep broke the stand, dismissing Duckett for 43. Crawley went on to register a fluent fifty but was eventually removed by Prasidh Krishna after scoring 64 runs off 57 balls.

Ollie Pope (22) and Joe Root (29) couldn’t convert their starts into substantial scores, and England kept losing wickets at regular intervals following the dismissals of the openers, courtesy of a superb bowling effort from Siraj and Prasidh Krishna. The pace duo picked up four wickets each to drag India back into the contest

Harry Brook was the only notable contributor with a valuable 53, pushing England to 247/9 before he was clean-bowled by Siraj.


India (Probable XI): Yashasvi Jaiswal, KL Rahul, B Sai Sudharsan, Shubman Gill (c), Ravindra Jadeja, Dhruv Jurel (wk), Washington Sundar, Shardul Thakur/Arshdeep Singh, Akash Deep, Mohammed Siraj, Jasprit Bumrah/Prasidh Krishna

snippet.description:

The album “Aadi Perukku - ஆடிப்பெருக்கு” is dedicated to Goddess Amman. This album has 9 songs sung by S.P.B, L.R Eswari, Mahanadhi Shobana, Bombay Saradha, P. Susheela, S. Janaki & Sakthi Dasan
Music By : Kanmani Raja D.V. Ramani, Aravind

Produced By : Unique Recording

Amman is the South Indian Goddess of Rain. She is the main South Indian mother/goddess in the southern India. Mari is closely associated with the Hindu goddess Parvati and Durga. Her festivals are held during the late summer/early autumn season of Aadi throughout Tamil Nadu and Deccan region, the largest being Aadi Thiruvizha. Devotees offer Pongal that is cooked using earthen pots which are made during the festive season. Rituals such as fire walking and mouth or nose piercing are also practised. Mari in Tamil means rain. Thus she is referred to as Mariyayee or Aathaa. Aathaa means mother or grandmother. She symbolizes sacrifice, motherhood, abundant wealth and good health. 

May Goddess Amman Bless You All ! Om Sakthi !

Amman is the South Indian Goddess of Rain. She is the main South Indian mother/goddess in the southern India. Mari is closely associated with the Hindu goddess Parvati and Durga. Her festivals are held during the late summer/early autumn season of Aadi throughout Tamil Nadu and Deccan region, the largest being Aadi Thiruvizha. Devotees offer Pongal that is cooked using earthen pots which are made during the festive season. Rituals such as fire walking and mouth or nose piercing are also practised. Mari in Tamil means rain. Thus she is referred to as Mariyayee or Aathaa. Aathaa means mother or grandmother. She symbolizes sacrifice, motherhood, abundant wealth and good health. 

May Goddess Amman Bless You All ! Om Sakthi !
